It combines four elements of sound : songs , instrumental music , sound effects , and , most importantly , the recorded voices of those who are the subjects of the documentary .
The latter element was revolutionary ; previous radio documentaries had used either professional voice actors or prepared scripts .
== Original radio ballads == The original radio ballads were recorded for the BBC .
The trio together made eight radio ballads between 1958 and 1964 .
All eight radio ballads were released on LP , by Argo Records , and later on CD .
A book about the making of the radio ballads was published on the fiftieth anniversary of the first broadcast of John Axon .
