In its simplest form , the Bo Diddley beat can be counted out as either a one-bar or a two-bar phrase .
Here is the count as a one-bar phrase : One e and ah , two e and ah , three e and ah , four e and ah ( the boldface counts are the clave rhythm ) .
In his other recordings , Bo Diddley used various rhythms , from straight back beat to pop ballad style to doo-wop , frequently with maracas by Jerome Green .
