Before late 1958 , rather than unified pop and country singles charts , Billboard had as many as four charts for each , separately ranking records according to sales , jukebox play , jockey spins ( i.e. , airplay ) , and , in the case of pop , a general `` Top 100 '' .
Presley discographer Ernst Jorgensen refers only to the Top 100 chart for pop hits .
